{
  "name": "The Drift Sea",
  "story": true,
  "chapter": 9,
  "title": "Chapter IX — The Drift Sea",
  "expedition": true,
  "theme": "saltworks",
  "objective": "Cross the Drift over open brine — skiff the pontoon causeways and raise the three drowned wave-logs to settle a corridor, then make landfall on the east shore.",
  "time": 900,
  "gate": {
    "need": 3
  },
  "captiveChars": [],
  "intro": [
    {
      "title": "Chapter IX — The Drift Sea",
      "lines": [
        "Act III. Past the last checkpoint, the map stops promising.",
        "The Drift: every wave that never settled, wide as a sea.",
        "Nothing out there is final. Bring finality with you."
      ],
      "art": "crossing"
    },
    {
      "title": "Last Light Pier",
      "lines": [
        "Skiffs from the pier. Shoal to shoal across the brine.",
        "Three drowned wave-logs sleep under the sheen — raise them and the corridor settles.",
        "Walk the causeway, not the sheen. Keep the signal alive."
      ],
      "art": "anchorcraft"
    }
  ],
  "outro": [
    {
      "title": "Across the Unsettled",
      "lines": [
        "The corridor settles: the wave-logs stand and the deep is simply crossed.",
        "Behind the crew, the buoys burn in a line — the first true road on the sea.",
        "Mid-Drift, an island of black glass glows. Names were burned there once."
      ],
      "art": "dawn"
    }
  ],
  "npcs": [
    {
      "id": "noor-avesh",
      "name": "Chartwright Noor Avesh",
      "lines": [
        "Noor Avesh, chartwright. Mind the maps — out here they redraw themselves while your back is turned.",
        "Past this pier, nothing has ever happened once and for all. That is the Drift. Sail accordingly.",
        "Three survey buoys went down with their wave-logs. Take a skiff, raise the logs, and my chart becomes a promise instead of a guess.",
        "Raise all three and a corridor settles east — you won't feel the crossing. You'll simply already be ashore.",
        "The deep takes no hull and no causeway that isn't settled. Three logs standing, or nothing."
      ],
      "gift": {
        "shards": 8
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "joss-maru",
      "name": "Joss Maru, Tidewarden",
      "lines": [
        "Tide's out. Tide's always out here. What comes in instead, we ring the bell for.",
        "The shoals hold. The sheen between them doesn't. Old Tarn's law travels: walk the causeway, not the sheen.",
        "Husks come up the channels glowing wrong — drift made flesh. Thin them on the water or meet them on your pier.",
        "Brine-hulks crust onto the spans and crack your barricades to salt. Keep the wave-logs standing and don't lean on a wall out here.",
        "Take these, salvage pay. Out here the LYTH remembers who carried it better than the sea remembers the ship."
      ],
      "gift": {
        "shards": 6
      }
    }
  ],
